eals, it became a more elite noblewomen's retreat. Grounded in archival research and extant paintings, drawings, prints and art objects from Corpus Domini, this volume explores the art, visual culture, and social history of an early modern Franciscan women's community.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 20. Sep 2019) 0aArt and religionzItalyzFerraraxHistoryy15th century. 0aMonasticism and religious orders for womenzItalyxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aNuns as artistszItalyzFerrara. 0aWomenxReligious lifezItalyzFerraraxHistory. 70(DE-601)1042216150(DE-588)4057542-1aStiftung2gnd 70(DE-601)1042803520(DE-588)4002851-3aArchitektur2gnd 70(DE-601)1056433000(DE-588)4138356-4aAusstattung2gnd 70(DE-601)1063597700(DE-588)4010109-5aChristliche Kunst2gnd 70(DE-601)5460684130(DE-588)7583222-7aKlosteranlage2gnd 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package 2016-2018z978311066731808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press  eBook Package 2018z978311060672008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2018 Englishz978311060403008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2018z9783110603149oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048534999zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048534999.jpg  a978-3-11-060403-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060672-0  Amsterdam University Press  eBook Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-066731-8  AUP eBook